1
00:00:00,140 --> 00:00:05,000
In this video we are going to do technical analysis of discount microservices.

2
00:00:05,030 --> 00:00:08,390
Let me start with the application architecture style.

3
00:00:08,420 --> 00:00:14,510
If you look at the application architecture style of discount microservices, we are going to use traditional

4
00:00:14,510 --> 00:00:16,040
and layered architecture.

5
00:00:16,040 --> 00:00:19,820
And layered architectures basically consists of three layers.

6
00:00:19,820 --> 00:00:24,140
These are the data access business layer and presentation layer.

7
00:00:24,680 --> 00:00:31,700
In data access layer, we will only database operations performed on this layer and this layer perform,

8
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:35,870
add, delete and update and extract data from the database.

9
00:00:36,440 --> 00:00:39,230
And after that we can implement Business layer.

10
00:00:39,230 --> 00:00:40,490
In business Layer.

11
00:00:40,490 --> 00:00:43,100
We will implement business logics on this layer.

12
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:49,100
And this layer will process the data taken by the data access and implement the actual logic and actual

13
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:50,870
use cases into our project.

14
00:00:51,380 --> 00:00:53,960
And after that we will implement presentation layer.

15
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:56,480
This layer includes the user interactions.

16
00:00:56,480 --> 00:01:00,530
It could be Windows Forms, Web applications or console application.

17
00:01:00,530 --> 00:01:07,160
But the main purpose is here to show the data to the user and transmit the data from the user to business

18
00:01:07,160 --> 00:01:08,750
layer and data access.

19
00:01:09,580 --> 00:01:13,900
And after that we can check pattern and principles of discount microservices.

20
00:01:13,930 --> 00:01:20,500
The first pattern is we will use gRPC protobuf files and endpoints for the inter service communication.

21
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:25,930
And after that we will use Entity Framework Core for all database operations.

22
00:01:25,930 --> 00:01:32,110
And we will use SQLite database which is embedded SQL database for efficient data storage.

23
00:01:32,140 --> 00:01:38,380
After that, we can check the libraries and NuGet packages that we are going to use for discount microservices.

24
00:01:38,410 --> 00:01:45,400
The first one is generic packages including Master and Fluent validation, and the second one is a gRPC

25
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:47,260
which is ASP.Net core gRPC.

26
00:01:47,260 --> 00:01:49,420
NuGet package comes from the template.

27
00:01:49,420 --> 00:01:55,480
And for database infrastructure operation we will use Entity Framework core SQLite provider.

28
00:01:55,480 --> 00:02:01,840
And we will use Entity Framework Core tools to migrate our database with discount operations.

29
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:05,320
And lastly we can check the project folder structure.

30
00:02:05,350 --> 00:02:07,990
Here you can see the our project folder structure.

31
00:02:07,990 --> 00:02:10,479
And we are planning to create these layers.

32
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:14,710
First of all we will create models folder including coupon entity.

33
00:02:14,710 --> 00:02:16,750
This will be the SQL entity.

34
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:22,270
And after that we will create data folder including Entity Framework, Core Data Context and Migration

35
00:02:22,270 --> 00:02:23,140
Extensions.

36
00:02:23,140 --> 00:02:30,130
And after that we will create services folder and these services folder including actual gRPC service

37
00:02:30,130 --> 00:02:31,150
implementation.

38
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:38,350
And we have Protoc folder and this protos folder including gRPC exposing API in proto files.

39
00:02:38,350 --> 00:02:42,010
So these are the layers that we are going to define.

40
00:02:42,010 --> 00:02:45,520
And we can map these layers into the layered architecture.

41
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:51,220
So that means in models folder we can say this is the domain layer and data folder this is the data

42
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:57,280
access layer and services folder are business layer and proto folder is representing our presentation

43
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:57,850
layer.

44
00:02:58,850 --> 00:03:02,600
After that we can check the deployment of the discount microservices.

45
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:07,340
Basically, we will containerize discount microservices with Docker and Docker file.

46
00:03:07,340 --> 00:03:13,760
And after that implement this Docker file and update our docker compose file for running discount microservices

47
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,430
and SQLite database in a Docker environment.

